@page "/how-it-works"
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]

<PageMeta Title="How ScamAlert works — watch family PCs"
          Description="Install on a loved one's Windows PC, add trusted contacts, and get SMS when suspicious remote access is detected."
          CanonicalPath="/how-it-works" />

<h1 class="h3 mb-3">How ScamAlert works</h1>
<p class="lead text-secondary">
    ScamAlert is for families who want to <strong>watch over</strong> a Windows PC used by someone they care about—without sitting behind them all day.
</p>

<div class="row g-4 mb-5">
    <div class="col-lg-8">
        <ol class="sa-steps">
            <li>
                <strong>Create your family account.</strong>
                Sign up, choose a plan, and add the people who should receive alerts (usually you and another trusted adult).
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Install on the PC you want to protect.</strong>
                Download the Windows app for Mom’s desktop, Dad’s laptop, or another machine. Link it to your account with the device key from your dashboard.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>We watch remote-access paths.</strong>
                When inbound remote desktop (RDP), SSH, or Telnet activity looks like an access attempt, the PC records it and your account is notified.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Your trusted contacts get SMS.</strong>
                Texts go to numbers you provide—not our staff. If the first person does not respond, we can escalate to the next contact you listed.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Your family decides what to do.</strong>
                Call your loved one, confirm whether they expected access, and help them hang up on the scammer or secure the machine.
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    <div class="col-lg-4">
        <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h2 class="h6">What we are (and are not)</h2>
                <ul class="small text-secondary mb-0">
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>We are</strong> an early-warning layer for remote access on PCs you choose.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>We are not</strong> antivirus, a VPN, or a guarantee that scams will never succeed.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2"><strong>We are not</strong> a monitoring service that reads their email or browses their files.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="sa-muted-panel rounded p-4 mb-4">
    <h2 class="h5">Why families use ScamAlert</h2>
    <p class="text-secondary mb-0">
        Refund scams and fake tech support often end with “install this so we can help.” If that happens while you are at work or in another state,
        ScamAlert gives your family a chance to <em>notice and respond</em> before a session turns into gift cards or drained accounts.
    </p>
</div>

<p class="mb-0">
    <a class="btn btn-primary me-2" href="/signup">Get started</a>
    <a class="btn btn-outline-secondary" href="/faq">Read FAQ</a>
</p>
